  "claim_short": "This packet proves an abstract lifting criterion for strongly split extensions of the form \\[ 0\\to J\\to A\\to \\widetilde E\\to 0, \\] where \\(E\\) has zero product. If a non-equivalent complete norm on the radical coordinate \\(E\\) makes the two \\(E\\)-module actions on \\(J\\) bounded, then the split algebra \\(A\\) has a non-equivalent complete algebra norm.",
